definition.value: The age at which some process, or disease started in a human individual.
The age, measured from some defined time point e.g. birth at which a subject (e.g. a human patient) is diagnosed with some disease e.g. breast cancer.

The percentage of subjects in a study who have survived without cancer spread for a defined period of time. Usually reported as time since diagnosis or treatment. Can be reported for an individual or a study population.

Progression free survival is a measurement from a defined time point e.g. diagnosis and indicates that the disease did not progress i.e. tumours did not increase in size and new incidences did not occur. PFS is usually used in analyzing results of treatment for advanced disease.
A temporal measurement related to disease progression
The point in time at which an individual was born.
A clinical temporal measurement indicating that the subject is alive at the end of the clinical investigation.
The recurrence of a disease after treatment
The point at which a clinical diagnosis is made.
The age at which death occurs.

The age of the conceptus, beginning from the time of FERTILIZATION. In clinical obstetrics, the gestational age is often estimated as the time from the last day of the last MENSTRUATION which is about 2 weeks before OVULATION and fertilization.
The age at which an alcohol diagnosis was made in a human patient
The age at which a breast cancer diagnosis was made in a human patient
The date or time of the last check of a patient by a medical professional.
The age of onset of (human) voice drop, the deepening of the voice of adolescents as they reach puberty
The age of an individual at the time an assessment takes place

quantification of some aspect of disease progression such as speed or symptom variability. Disease progression can be quantified in a number of ways, for example as a correlated measure of progression scores from different symptom areas
A disease involving the female reproductive system.

The process by which information about the health status of an individual is obtained after a study has officially closed; an activity that continues something that has already begun or that repeats something that has already been done. [def-source: NCI]
EFO:0009642 'follow-up' refers to the medical procedure process of running follow-ups; EFO:0030038 'follow up status' refers to an observed quality.
The age of a person's father at which father's death occurred.
The age of onset of first facial hair.
The age of a person's mother at which mother's death occurred.
Death in during childhood, defined here as between the ages of 2 and 10 years.
The determination of the amount of eicosanoids present in a sample, typically blood
The determination of the amount of prostaglandins present in a sample, typically blood
Age at initiation of a medical treatment, such as a drug, therapy or medical device.

label.value: age at initiation of hormone replacement therapy

definition.value: Age at initiation of hormone replacement therapy, the therapeutic use of hormones to alleviate the effects of hormone deficiency.

label.value: age at initiation of corrective lens use

definition.value: Age at initiation of the use of corrective lenses, such as glasses or contact lenses, to treat an abnormality of the eye.

label.value: age at initiation of oral contraceptive pill use

definition.value: Age at initiation of the use of an oral contraceptive pill.
Age at the time of a specific medical procedure or intervention intended to alter the course of a disease.
Age of initation of the habit of smoking, the inhaling and exhaling of tobacco smoke.

label.value: age at initiation of cannabis use

definition.value: Age of initiation of the consumption of the drug cannabis.
the ending of pregnancy by removing a fetus or embryo before it can survive outside the uterus.
Base class for definitions.
A named element in the model.
Usage example and description.
An attributed label.
A permissible value, accompanied by intended text and an optional mapping to a concept URI.
A collection of subset, type, slot and class definitions.
The definition of a property or a slot.
